records.addlTxt: Defendant Travis T. Ranson in court with attorney Brian David Van Ells.  Defendant Travis T. Ranson in custody.  Raymond Pelrine appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Minute sheet. State dismisses second and subsequent offense enhancer, gives plea agreement.  Court questions defendant on change of plea.  Rights/elements/max. penalties reviewed with defendant.  Defendant enters guilty plea.  Defense stipulates to factual basis to accept plea.  Court finds plea made freely, knowingly and voluntarily, accepts plea, and finds guilty of Ct. 1 w/o the second and subsequent enhancer.  Court reviews collateral consequences of felony conviction, possible penalties. Defendant must have a DNA sample on file with the State of Wisconsin and pay a DNA surcharge. State/Defense ready to proceed to sentencing without the benefit of a PSI. State/Defense give joint sentencing recommendation. Court makes statement, imposes sentence. Bond is no longer in effect.

Defendant Travis T. Ranson in court with attorney Brian David Van Ells.  Joan M. Korb appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court reviews events in file. Atty Van Ells indicates defendant has not had surgery yet because of a scheduling problem with his doctor. Atty Van Ells indicates matter is resolved, requests another adjournment to early December to allow defendant to have the surgery and work out some workmans comp issues.  State concerned that case has been pending for almost a year now but will go along with one more adjournment.  Status conference scheduled for December 21, 2015 at 03:30 pm.

Defendant Travis T. Ranson in court with attorney Brian David Van Ells.  Joan M. Korb appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court reviews events in file. Atty Van Ells indicates defendant is having surgery next week, asks court to set matter off for 6 to 8 weeks. Atty Van Ells feels matter will resolve short of trial. State has no objection to adjournment. Bond remains in effect.  Status conference scheduled for September 24, 2015 at 09:30 am.

Defendant Travis T. Ranson in court with attorney Brian David Van Ells.  Raymond Pelrine appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court reviews events in file. Atty Van Ells requests a 30-45 continuance to allow him time to get up to speed on the case. State has no objection. Bond remains in effect.  Status conference scheduled for July 16, 2015 at 09:30 am.

Defendant Travis T. Ranson in court with attorney Gregory A. Gerbers.  Joan M. Korb appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court reviews events in file. Bond remains in effect.  Status conference scheduled for May 22, 2015 at 09:30 am.
